  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "as a validator, I want corrupted files to be able to be repaired\nso that I don't have to manually find and delete corrupt files.\n\n- should warn about clock skew, and once accepting the risk we can update the slashing protection files\n\n - update invalid files by default (files that can't be parsed, eg 0 sized files), values should be written to the next epoch\n\n - potentially have a `-a` option to update all the valid files as well\n\n- potentially require a flag to cleanup lock files, and should respect file locking by default in case someone tries to run the subcommand while teku is online.\n\n - potentially allow user to set a (future) epoch",
